            "creation_date": 1401893620,
            "body": "<p>An abstract class can not be instantiated with <code>new<\/code>. That's the whole point of the <code>abstract<\/code> keyword. <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/IandI/abstract.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">The official Java tutorial<\/a> reads:<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>An abstract class is a class that is declared abstract\u2014it may or may not include abstract methods. Abstract classes cannot be instantiated, but they can be subclassed.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>When you want to create instances of a class which are exactly that class and none of its subclasses, then do not declare it as abstract.<\/p>\n\n<p>When you would like to keep your <code>Cell<\/code> class abstract for some reason, you could create an additional <code>class SimpleCell extends Cell<\/code> (or another appropriate name) and use this to represent the diagonals in your table.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 24040804,
            "question_id": 24040681,
            "last_edit_date": 1401894073
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e534287e898051c47acadf1ee9644785?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 1638510,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1511403,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1511403/t-g",
                "reputation": 1931,
                "display_name": "T.G",
                "accept_rate": 75
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1401895521,
            "creation_date": 1401894646,
            "body": "<p><code>public abstract class Cell{...}<\/code> cannot have it's own instance, because of the <code>abstract<\/code> modifier.  When you writing <code>public abstract class MyClass<\/code> you're telling, that you're creating a type, that will by extended by other classes, but pure object of <code>Cell<\/code> are not allowed. More about it <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1352109/java-abstract-modifier\">in this other StackOverflow question<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n<p>Solution:<\/p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><p>remove abstract modifier (code works right after doing it, if there ware no methods defined with abstract modifier).<\/p><\/li>\n<li><p>create other type like <code>public class MiddleCell extends Cell<\/code>. and in code <code>table[i][j] = new MiddleCell();<\/code><\/p><\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n<p>P.S. if it has to be an abstract class, I would recommend renaming it to <code>AbstractCell<\/code><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 24041165,
            "question_id": 24040681,
            "last_edit_date": 1495541108
        }
    ],
